Exemplo de Análise Bibliométrica

- Termos Buscados (String)

Analisar a Literatura sobre Internet of Things e Costumização em Massa utilizando documentos da WoS e Scopus, Termos de busca (String):

  • TS=(( “IoT” OR “Internet of Things”) AND ( “distributed manufacturing” OR “mass customization”)) = 57

  • TITLE-ABS-KEY-AUTH(( “IoT” OR “Internet of Things”) AND ( “distributed manufacturing” OR “mass customization”)) = 80

Carregamento de Dados e Conversão

library(bibliometrix) # pacote para análise bibliométrica
## Warning: package 'bibliometrix' was built under R version 3.5.3
## To cite bibliometrix in publications, please use:
## 
## Aria, M. & Cuccurullo, C. (2017) bibliometrix: An R-tool for comprehensive science mapping analysis, Journal of Informetrics, 11(4), pp 959-975, Elsevier.
##                         
## 
## http:\\www.bibliometrix.org
## 
##                         
## To start with the shiny web-interface, please digit:
## biblioshiny()
# Ler bases

b1 <- readFiles("savedrecs.bib") # WoS

b2 <- readFiles("scopus.bib") # Scopus

# Converter pra dataframe

# colocar base "isi" ou "scopus"
# e o formato "bibtex" ou "plaintext"

c1 <- convert2df(b1, dbsource="isi",format="bibtex") # WoS
## 
## Converting your isi collection into a bibliographic dataframe
## 
## Articles extracted   57 
## Done!
## 
## 
## Generating affiliation field tag AU_UN from C1:  Done!
c2 <- convert2df(b2, dbsource="scopus",format="bibtex") # Scopus
## 
## Converting your scopus collection into a bibliographic dataframe
## 
## Articles extracted   80 
## Done!
## 
## 
## Generating affiliation field tag AU_UN from C1:  Done!
# Unir e remover duplicatas

M <- mergeDbSources(c1, c2, remove.duplicated=TRUE)
## 
##  42 duplicated documents have been removed

Principais características (Análise Descritiva)

Gráficos (Análise Descritiva)

plot(x=results, k=10, pause=F)

Rede de cocitação

NetMatrix <- biblioNetwork(M, analysis = "co-citation",
                           network = "references", sep = ";")

net=networkPlot(NetMatrix, n = 30, Title = "Co-Citation Network",
                type = "fruchterman", size.cex=TRUE, size=20,
                remove.multiple=FALSE, labelsize=0.7,edgesize = 5,
                edges.min=2)

Historiograph - Direct citation linkages

histResults <- histNetwork(M, min.citations=quantile(M$TC,0.7), sep = ";")
## Articles analysed   36
options(width = 130)

net <- histPlot(histResults, n=20, size.cex=TRUE, size = 5,
                labelsize = 3, arrowsize = 1)
